On Tuesday, September 14, voters will head to the polls to vote on two questions: 1) Do you want to recall Governor Gavin Newsom? and 2) If the governor is recalled, who do you want to replace him? All eligible registered state voters will receive a vote-by-mail ballot ahead of the election, and county elections offices have already begun to mail out ballots. For more information, please visit https://www.sos.ca.gov/elections

Keep it here for the latest news and updates on the gubernatorial recall.
